g.text: Title: Schematic of Xling, a pocket demon
Regulator of the battery charge current:
This circuit produces +3.3V and charges a battery when
connected to USB. This can be done by providing a +5V USB
(+4.9V...+4.6V after a voltage drop on D1) to fill needs of the
whole circuit via U4 (AP3401, DC-DC buck converter) and
charge a single-cell 3.7V Li-Ion battery using U3 (MCP73831
charge controller, Q1 is closed). An under-voltage lockout
(UVLO) circuit of U4 prevents a deep battery discharge when
input voltage drops to +2.7V or below.
MCU (128 KiB flash, 16 KiB SRAM, 4KiB EEPROM)
